1578
01:30:22,515 --> 01:30:24,783
Turns out, the Higgs mass

1579
01:30:24,784 --> 01:30:27,286
is about as interesting
as it could be.

1580
01:30:27,287 --> 01:30:30,121
It's sort of in no man's land.

1581
01:30:30,122 --> 01:30:32,291
It doesn't prefer symmetries,

1582
01:30:32,292 --> 01:30:34,160
and it doesn't prefer
multiverse,

1583
01:30:34,161 --> 01:30:35,862
but it's right in the middle.

1584
01:30:35,863 --> 01:30:39,764
The data is puzzling enough

1585
01:30:39,765 --> 01:30:44,636
that it hasn't excluded
any of the theories

1586
01:30:44,637 --> 01:30:46,138
I was involved with,

1587
01:30:46,139 --> 01:30:48,374
but it hasn't
confirmed them either.

1588
01:30:48,375 --> 01:30:52,644
